  • Constructor Details

    • TagDescription

      public TagDescription​(ByteBuffer buffer, HasChipLocation src, InetAddress host, int tag) throws UnknownHostException
      Parameters:
      buffer - The buffer to parse.
      src - What chip did this come from?
      host - What address did that chip have? (Only for creating a Tag.)
      tag - What was the tag ID? (Only for creating a Tag.)
      Throws:
      UnknownHostException - If we can't parse the host. Unexpected.

  • Method Details

    • isInUse

      public boolean isInUse()
      Returns:
      True if the tag is marked as being in use.

    • isTemporary

      public boolean isTemporary()
      Returns:
      True if the tag is temporary.

    • isARP

      public boolean isARP()
      Returns:
      True if the tag is in the ARP state (where the MAC address is being looked up; this is a transient state so unlikely).

    • isReverse

      public boolean isReverse()
      Returns:
      True if the tag is a reverse tag.

    • isStrippingSDP

      public boolean isStrippingSDP()
      Returns:
      True if the tag is to strip the SDP header.

    • getTag

      public Tag getTag()
      Get the standard tag descriptor. Not properly meaningful unless the tag is in use.
      Returns:
      The tag descriptor. May be an IPTag or a ReverseIPTag.
